        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-31T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-31T07:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/8–3149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-31T13:00:00+01:00">August 31, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3478. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3047 August 24, 8 p. m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d87fn1">It repeated telegram 436, <ref target="#pg_147">p.
                            147</ref>.</note> re Chinese proposal introduce Sino-Soviet treaty
                    questions in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Embassy officer had informal
                    discussion Dening<note n="2" xml:id="d87fn2">Maberly E. Dening, British
                        Assistant Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs (Far East).</note>
                    this matter. Dening stated Foreign Office questioned what concrete results
                    Chinese expected to flow from such move. Debate in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> would not restore Chinese rights Manchuria. Therefore Foreign
                    Office did not agree to support or not to support Chinese proposal. Dening,
                    however, agreed debate <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> would provide western
                    powers with opportunity for propaganda vs Soviet imperialism.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
